               <p>JOHN VICKERY BROUGHTON. On the 21st of April I was in <placeName id="t18270531-95-crimeloc479">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-95-crimeloc479" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-95-crimeloc479" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-95-off477 t18270531-95-crimeloc479"></join>, about seven o'clock in the evening - I had a handkerchief in my pocket; I felt something behind me - I turned round immediately, and took my handkerchief out of the prisoner's hands - I know it to be mine; there were several others in company with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-95-person639">
                  EDWARD 
                  BOOTHMAN
               <interp inst="t18270531-95-person639" type="surname" value="BOOTHMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-95-person639" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-95-person639" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I have the handkerchief, which was brought to the watch-house with the prisoner.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking along, and saw a boy pick the gentleman's pocket - I was going to tell the gentleman of it; he threw it down, and I took it up to give it to him.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
